form.text: The composition of the present invention preferably
contains an acid diffusion control agent (D). The acid diffu›
sion control agent (D) acts as a quencher that traps acids
generated from the acid generator or the like upon exposure
and inhibits a reaction of the acid-decomposable resin in the
unexposed area by extra generated acids. As the acid diffusion
control agent (D), a basic compound, a low-molecular com›
pound which has a nitrogen atom and a group capable of
leaving by the action of an acid, a basic compound whose
basicity is reduced or lost upon irradiation with active light or
radiation, or an onium salt which becomes a relatively weak
acid with respect to the acid generator can be used.
